Tom, nothing you said about Barry I would dispute, other than our definition of racism and the fact that the different degrees of racism exists, but by any other name it still is racism. I definitely would never call Barry a white supremist as I also have dealt with those. But all this has all been hashed out elsewhere. And I recognize all his efforts and successes. There is no criticism in my post. He is the first to admit that he came on site with a set of ideas and values that has been remolded as a result of contact with various folks on that thread, particularly veterans. What I seek is the reason why Doc Barry Spatz became the individual that he was when he FIRST put his first post on this site from his early days, not who he is today. Who he is now and who he was when he he came on site are two different individuals. We all can see this. Who he was when a young student and who he was when he first came on site, are two different people. I can see this. This is what I am curious about.<br><br>
And, note that I said &quot;a smiggen of solice and comfort&quot; which would indicate that I definitely would not tout this loudly from my soapbox, but whatever the politicians feared in Desert Storm or anything else they contemplated between Vietnam and Desert Storm, the outcome is the same; lives saved because they treaded lightly. That is my only consideration and what really matters. And this as a result from Vietnam.
